title: Complete coverage: Belvidere downs Roselle Park to win third straight football game
text:
Complete Box Score Â» 
Belvidere charged to its third straight win Friday night, jumping out to a 21-point lead and rolling from there to defeat Roselle Park 33-14 in a key Mid-State 38 Valley Division football game. 
The County Seaters (3-2) needed the win to keep their chances of a North 2 Group 1 sectional playoff spot in good health. They did so behind big plays from quarterback Jake Thornton and running back Tommy Madeo and a physically dominating display on both lines. 
Follow the links below for complete coverage of the Belvidere win.
